# Internationalization (i18n)

## Brand

- Business name: **Sevinc Picnic**
- Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/sevinc_picnic (handle `@sevinc_picnic`)
- Tagline (RU bio): atmosphere for your celebration — reflect in copy, not generic US picnic template

## Services (all locales must match)

1. Decorated **photo zone** in picnic design
2. **Event design & organization** — birthdays, marry-me proposals, outdoor parties and meetups
3. **Picnic equipment rental**

Pricing is **on request** — no fixed USD prices in copy.

## Languages

- **Default**: Uzbek (`uz`) — shown on first visit
- **Additional**: Russian (`ru`), English (`en`)

## Where strings live

- All user-facing copy goes in `src/i18n/locales/{uz,ru,en}.ts`
- Shared shape is defined in `src/i18n/types.ts` as `Translations`
- Components use `useI18n()` from `src/i18n/context.tsx` — never hardcode UI strings in `.tsx` files

## Adding or changing text

1. Add the key to `Translations` in `types.ts`
2. Add the string to **all three** locale files (`uz`, `ru`, `en`)
3. Use `t.section.key` in the component

## Locale switcher

- `LanguageSwitcher` in the navbar; choice persists in `localStorage` under `picnic-locale`
- `document.documentElement.lang` and page `<title>` / meta description update with the active locale

## Do not

- Introduce a fourth language without updating `Locale`, `locales`, `localeLabels`, and all locale files
- Leave one locale file out of sync when adding keys
